# Component Patterns and Conventions

## Component Structure

All components follow this pattern:

```javascript
import styles from './ComponentName.module.scss';
// Other imports...

const ComponentName = () => {
  return (
    <section className={`${styles.ComponentName}`}>
      {/* Component content */}
    </section>
  )
}

export default ComponentName;
```

## Naming Conventions

- **Components**: PascalCase (e.g., `Hero`, `RegisterCTA`)
- **Files**: Match component name (e.g., `Hero.js`, `Hero.module.scss`)
- **CSS Classes**: PascalCase in SCSS modules (e.g., `.Hero`, `.Content`)
- **Directories**: Match component name (e.g., `Hero/`, `RegisterCTA/`)

## Layout Pattern

Pages use a custom layout pattern:

```javascript
// In page component
const PageComponent = () => {
  return (
    <div>
      {/* Page content */}
    </div>
  )
}

PageComponent.getLayout = function getLayout(page) {
  return (
    <RootLayout>
      {page}
    </RootLayout>
  );
}

export default PageComponent;
```

## Component Organization

- Each component in its own directory
- SCSS modules for component-specific styles
- Import global styles in `_app.js`
- Use Bootstrap classes combined with custom SCSS modules

## Section Structure

Most components are sections with:
- Section wrapper with component-specific class
- Section heading with `.section-heading` class
- Background images and shades for visual effects
- Responsive margins and padding

